COHEN, Respondent, v. HOLTZER, Appellant. (City Court of New York,

General Term.

May 28, 1900.) Action by Morris Cohen against Max Holtzer. Ekom an order of reference in favor of plaintiff, defendant appeals. Reversed. Ignace I. Apfel, for appellant. Max Altmayer, for respondent. PER CURIAM.

Order of reference appealed from is reversed, with costs and disbursements, and the motion for a reference, etc., is denied, without costs.
